    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Adopting strict concurrency in Swift 6 apps"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Strict concurrency checking in the Swift 6 language mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "helps you find and fix data races at compile time.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Overlapping access to shared mutable state",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "creates the risk for data races.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Data races can cause your app to crash, misbehave, or corrupt user data.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Because data races depend on the ordering of concurrent operations,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "they can be very difficult to reproduce and debug.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Strict concurrency checking lets you confirm,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "when you compile your app,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that its code is free from data races.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When you identify a data race,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you fix it by eliminating overlapping access, shared access, or mutable state.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about the language-level concurrency model in Swift,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/LanguageGuide/Concurrency.html",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The Swift Programming Language",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Decide-when-to-upgrade-to-strict-checking",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Decide when to upgrade to strict checking",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Xcode 16 supports the new Swift 6 language mode,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "which uses strict checking for concurrency,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and it also still includes the Swift 5, 4.2, and 4 language modes.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The Swift 6 language mode is opt-in:",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Your projects continue to build with their current language mode,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and new projects default to the Swift 5 language mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Adopting the Swift 6 language mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "can significantly improve the quality of your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "by catching mistakes in concurrent code at compile time.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "It can be especially useful",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "if you’re experiencing hard-to-reproduce crashes",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and want to methodically eliminate the risk of data races.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If you’re actively working on integrating more concurrency",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to improve responsiveness and performance,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "adopting the Swift 6 language mode can ensure that those changes",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "don’t risk introducing new data races.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If your app is organized into multiple modules,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you can migrate your code one module at a time.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "It’s usually easier to migrate the app first,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and the migrate the modules it depends on.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you maintain a public Swift package,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "adopting the Swift 6 language mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "helps your users who want to migrate their codebases too.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "You can follow along on the adoption of the Swift 6 language",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in popular packages on ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SwiftPackageIndex.com",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Upgrade-a-project-to-Swift-6",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Upgrade a project to Swift 6",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can start using new features from Swift 6,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "like strict concurrency checking,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "before upgrading your project to the Swift 6 language mode.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To enable new language features,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "open your build settings, and choose Swift Compiler - Upcoming Features;",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "then select Yes next to the features you want to adopt.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "As you prepare to upgrade to the Swift 6 language version,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you can increase the level of concurrency checking",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "by changing the Strict Concurrency Checking build setting",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "from Minimal to Complete.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "AdoptingSwift6-features",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To upgrade your project to the Swift 6 language mode,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "open your build settings, and choose",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Swift Compiler - Language > Swift Language Version.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "AdoptingSwift6-language",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Upgrading to the Swift 6 language mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "enables all of the new language features that are part of Swift 6,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "including strict concurrency checking.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "After you upgrade,",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "the list of upcoming features still includes a few features",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "that will be part of a future Swift version,",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "which are disabled by default in the Swift 6 language mode.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After you turn on strict concurrency checking,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you might see a large number of new compiler errors and warnings.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "However,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "fixing the data race in one part of your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "often resolves multiple reported errors.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "You don’t have to fix all of the reported data races at once.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If you need to, you can fix some of them now,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "switch back to the Swift 5 language mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or switch back to minimal concurrency checking,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and then continue fixing the remaining data races later.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about how to migrate,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "including techniques for interoperating with code",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that hasn’t yet migrated to strict checking,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://swift.org/migration",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
